<subSubSection id="C376F389FFC8FF86FDB7FD396CD6F878" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="588" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD3A002FFC8FF87FDB7FD396CE2FAD1" blockId="0.[151,1436,750,2022]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">
popularly known as Pitu, Bristled River Shrimp and Buchura River Prawn, is a freshwater shrimp species widespread along the eastern coasts of the Americas. The species can be found from the southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="F37BE092FFC8FF87FEEAFCE269FEFA0A" box="[296,446,820,843]" name="United States of America" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">United States</collectingCountry>
, where the prawns were introduced (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFDDDF3FFC8FF87FCA6FCE26CF8FA0A" author="Holthuis" box="[868,1208,820,843]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Holthuis, L. B. &amp; Provenzano, A. J. (1970) New distribution records for species of Macrobrachium with notes on the distribution of the genus in Florida (Decapoda, Palaemonidae). Crustaceana, 19 (2), 211 - 213. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1163 / 156854070 X 00545" type="journal article" year="1970">
Holthuis &amp; Provenzano, 
<number id="3DA4B225FFC8FF87FBBDFCE26CF8FA0A" box="[1151,1208,820,843]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="1970.0">1970</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), southwards to Rio Grande do Sul (
<collectingCountry id="F37BE092FFC8FF87FE81FC8169C9FA2F" box="[323,393,855,878]" name="Brazil" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">Brazil</collectingCountry>
), including numerous records in 
<collectingCountry id="F37BE092FFC8FF87FD2FFC816B01FA2F" box="[749,833,855,878]" name="Mexico" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F37BE092FFC8FF87FC8FFC816BFDFA2F" box="[845,957,855,878]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F37BE092FFC8FF87FC0BFC816C00FA2F" box="[969,1088,855,878]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F37BE092FFC8FF87FB8FFC816CE4FA2F" box="[1101,1188,855,878]" name="Panama" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">Panama</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F37BE092FFC8FF87FB72FC816D5CFA2F" box="[1200,1308,855,878]" name="Colombia" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F37BE092FFC8FF87FAE5FC816DD7FA2F" box="[1319,1431,855,878]" name="Venezuela" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F37BE092FFC8FF87FF55FCAF68AAFAD1" box="[151,234,889,912]" name="Guyana" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">Guyana</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F37BE092FFC8FF87FEDFFCAF69C3FAD1" box="[285,387,889,912]" name="Suriname" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">Suriname</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFDDDF3FFC8FF87FE50FCAF6A74FAD1" author="Holthuis" box="[402,564,889,912]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Holthuis, L. B. (1952) A general revision of the Palaemonidae (Crustacea, Decapoda, Natantia) of the Americas II. The subfamilies Palaemonidae. Occasional Paper, Allan Hancock Foundation Publications, 12, 1 - 396." type="journal article" year="1952">
Holthuis, 
<number id="3DA4B225FFC8FF87FE3EFCAF6A74FAD1" box="[508,564,889,912]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="1952.0">1952</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFDDDF3FFC8FF87FDFDFCAF6AA7FAD1" author="Williams" box="[575,743,889,912]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Williams, A. B. (1984) Shrimps, Lobsters, and Crabs of the Atlantic Coast of the Eastern United States, Maine to Florida. Smithsonian Institution Press. 550 pp." type="book" year="1984">
Williams, 
<number id="3DA4B225FFC8FF87FD6CFCAF6AA7FAD1" box="[686,743,889,912]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFDDDF3FFC8FF87FD33FCAF6B2FFAD1" author="Melo" box="[753,879,889,912]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Melo, G. A. S. (2003) Familias Atyidae, Palaemonidae e Sergestidae. In: Melo, G. A. S. (Ed.), Manual de identificacao dos Crustacea Decapoda de agua doce do Brasil. Editora Loyola, pp. 289 - 415." type="book chapter" year="2003">
Melo, 
<number id="3DA4B225FFC8FF87FCF4FCAF6B2FFAD1" box="[822,879,889,912]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFDDDF3FFC8FF87FCB8FCAF6CD6FAD1" author="Valencia" box="[890,1174,889,912]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Valencia, D. &amp; Campos, M. R. (2007) Freshwater prawns of the genus Macrobrachium Bate, 1868 (Crustacea: Decapoda: Palaemonidae) of Colombia. Zootaxa, 1456, 1 - 44." type="journal article" year="2007">
Valencia &amp; Campos, 
<number id="3DA4B225FFC8FF87FB9EFCAF6CD6FAD1" box="[1116,1174,889,912]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD3A002FFC8FF87FF05FC4A6996FD21" blockId="0.[151,1436,750,2022]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">
This species was described about two hundred years ago by Arend Friedrich August 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFDDDF3FFC8FF87FB98FC4A6D5EFAF2" author="Wiegmann" box="[1114,1310,924,947]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Wiegmann, A. F. (1836) Beschreibung einiger neuen Crustaceen des Berliner Museums aus Mexico und Brasilien. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, 2, 145 - 151." type="journal article" year="1836">
Wiegmann, (
<number id="3DA4B225FFC8FF87FB26FC4A6D5EFAF2" box="[1252,1310,924,947]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="1836.0">1836</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number id="3DA4B225FFC8FF87FAEBFC4A6D14FAF2" box="[1321,1364,924,947]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="150.0">150</number>
), from specimens collected on the “Brazilian coast”, with no further location details. Its taxonomic history is complex with a long list of rearrangements and synonymies (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFDDDF3FFC8FF87FD09FC376B33FAB9" author="Holthuis" box="[715,883,993,1016]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Holthuis, L. B. (1952) A general revision of the Palaemonidae (Crustacea, Decapoda, Natantia) of the Americas II. The subfamilies Palaemonidae. Occasional Paper, Allan Hancock Foundation Publications, 12, 1 - 396." type="journal article" year="1952">
Holthuis, 
<number id="3DA4B225FFC8FF87FCF8FC376B33FAB9" box="[826,883,993,1016]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="1952.0">1952</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number id="3DA4B225FFC8FF87FC41FC376B84FAB9" box="[899,964,993,1016]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="96.0" valueMax="97.0" valueMin="95.0">95-97</number>
; references above). Due to a great many morphological variations, misidentifications and uncertainties that were detected around the relationship and the evolution of this species, members of this group are categorized as the 
<taxonomicName id="4C6CDB81FFC8FF87FC5BFBF16C48FD7F" box="[921,1032,1062,1086]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palaemonidae" genus="Macrobrachium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olfersii">
<emphasis id="B9187C10FFC8FF87FC5BFBF16C48FD7F" box="[921,1032,1062,1086]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">M. olfersii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFDDDF3FFC8FF87FBBEFBF1698BFD21" author="Rossi" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Rossi, N. &amp; Mantelatto, F. L. (2013) Molecular analysis of the freshwater prawn Macrobrachium olfersii (Decapoda, Palaemonidae) supports the existence of a single species throughout its distribution. PLoS ONE, 8 (1), e 54698. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0054698" type="journal article" year="2013">
Rossi &amp; Mantelatto, 
<number id="3DA4B225FFC8FF87FA9DFBF16DD8FD7F" box="[1375,1432,1063,1086]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="2013.0">2013</number>
; Rossi &amp; Mantelatto, in prep.
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD3A002FFC8FF87FF05FBBA6C5AFDAA" blockId="0.[151,1436,750,2022]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">
Although many of the numerous taxonomic controversies have been corrected in recent years by a combination of different analyses, the nomenclature of this species still appears troubled. In recent systematic literature treating the species, two spelling variants exist: with two “i” (
<taxonomicName id="4C6CDB81FFC8FF87FD6EFB666AB7FD89" box="[684,759,1200,1224]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palaemonidae" genus="Macrobrachium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olfersii">
<emphasis id="B9187C10FFC8FF87FD6EFB666AB7FD89" box="[684,759,1200,1224]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">olfersii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFDDDF3FFC8FF87FCF1FB676C17FD89" author="De" box="[819,1111,1201,1224]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="De Grave, S. &amp; Fransen, C. H. J. M. (2011) Carideorum catalogus: the recent species of the dendrobranchiate, stenopodidean, procaridean and caridean shrimps (Crustacea: Decapoda). Zoologische Mededelingen, 89 (5), 195 - 589. Avaliable from: http: // www. zoologischemededelingen. nl / 85 / nr 02 / a 01 (Accessed 23 May 2016)" type="journal article" year="2011">
<collectingCountry id="F37BE092FFC8FF87FCF1FB676B12FD89" box="[819,850,1201,1224]" name="South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">De</collectingCountry>
Grave &amp; Fransen, 
<number id="3DA4B225FFC8FF87FBDDFB676C17FD89" box="[1055,1111,1201,1224]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFDDDF3FFC8FF87FBA3FB676D37FD89" author="Rossi" box="[1121,1399,1201,1224]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Rossi, N. &amp; Mantelatto, F. L. (2013) Molecular analysis of the freshwater prawn Macrobrachium olfersii (Decapoda, Palaemonidae) supports the existence of a single species throughout its distribution. PLoS ONE, 8 (1), e 54698. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0054698" type="journal article" year="2013">
Rossi &amp; Mantelatto, 
<number id="3DA4B225FFC8FF87FA82FB676D37FD89" box="[1344,1399,1201,1224]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="2013.0">2013</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) as an ending or only one (
<taxonomicName id="4C6CDB81FFC8FF87FE4DFB056993FDAA" box="[399,467,1235,1259]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palaemonidae" genus="Macrobrachium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olfersi">
<emphasis id="B9187C10FFC8FF87FE4DFB056993FDAA" box="[399,467,1235,1259]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">olfersi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFDDDF3FFC8FF87FDCFFB026B75FDAA" author="Pileggi" box="[525,821,1236,1259]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Pileggi, L. G. &amp; Mantelatto, F. L. (2010) Molecular phylogeny of the freshwater prawn genus Macrobrachium (Decapoda, Palaemonidae), with emphasis on the relationships among selected American species. Invertebrate Systematics, 24 (1), 194 - 208. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 09043" type="journal article" year="2010">
Pileggi &amp; Mantelatto, 
<number id="3DA4B225FFC8FF87FD3EFB026B75FDAA" box="[764,821,1236,1259]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFDDDF3FFC8FF87FCFDFB026C4EFDAA" author="Pileggi" box="[831,1038,1235,1259]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Pileggi, L. G. &amp; Mantelatto, F. L. (2012) Taxonomic revision of doubtful Brazilian freshwater shrimp species of genus Macrobrachium (Decapoda, Palaemonidae). Iheringia, Serie Zoologia, 102 (4), 426 - 437. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0073 - 47212012005000012" type="journal article" year="2012">
Pileggi 
<emphasis id="B9187C10FFC8FF87FC53FB026B80FDAA" box="[913,960,1235,1259]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">et al</emphasis>
., 
<number id="3DA4B225FFC8FF87FC16FB026C4EFDAA" box="[980,1038,1236,1259]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="2012.0">2012</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD3A002FFC8FF87FF05FB216B5DFF28" blockId="0.[151,1436,750,2022]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">
This nomenclatorial confusion is obviously not of recent making, as numerous examples exist throughout the literature of either spelling variant, but clearly not linked to any biological discipline. We noted that the two distinct names can be found throughout different research studies with no consistent usage within the same discipline. Here we list some examples which adopted 
<taxonomicName id="4C6CDB81FFC8FF87FDC9FA896A32FC37" box="[523,626,1374,1398]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palaemonidae" genus="Macrobrachium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olfersi">
<emphasis id="B9187C10FFC8FF87FDC9FA896A32FC37" box="[523,626,1374,1398]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">M. olfersi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(- 
<emphasis id="B9187C10FFC8FF87FD48FA896AD1FC37" box="[650,657,1375,1398]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">i</emphasis>
) or 
<taxonomicName id="4C6CDB81FFC8FF87FD7CFA896B6CFC37" box="[702,812,1374,1398]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palaemonidae" genus="Macrobrachium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olfersii">
<emphasis id="B9187C10FFC8FF87FD7CFA896B6CFC37" box="[702,812,1374,1398]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">M. olfersii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(- 
<emphasis id="B9187C10FFC8FF87FC87FA896B14FC37" box="[837,852,1375,1398]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">ii</emphasis>
). Studies involving physiology used - 
<emphasis id="B9187C10FFC8FF87FB2AFA896CAFFC37" box="[1256,1263,1375,1398]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">i</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFDDDF3FFC8FF87FB3CFA89688EFCD9" author="Augusto" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Augusto, A., Greene, L. J., Laure, H. J. &amp; McNamara, J. C. (2007) The ontogeny of isosmotic intracellular regulation in the diadromous freshwater palaemonid shrimps, Macrobrachium amazonicum and M. olfersi (Decapoda). Journal of Crustacean Biology, 27 (4), 626 - 634. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1651 / S- 2796.1" type="journal article" year="2007">
Augusto 
